This paper discusses techniques for tuning consistency and latency in distributed NoSQL storage systems, which are typically used in web applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also focuses on database systems and consistency models, which suggests cs.DB (Databases) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as likely categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of consistency on application-level service level agreements (SLAs), which suggests cs.SE (Software Engineering) as a possible category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel technique for tuning consistency and latency, which involves probabilistic choices, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible category.
